The '''dense essence mine''' is located north-east of [[Arceuus]]. The mine contains two dense runestones, where players can mine [[dense essence block]]s, which are then used on the [[Dark Altar]] to create [[dark essence block]]s. It is not possible to get a [[rock golem]] pet from mining here.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/761138207593533440|date=4 August 2016|archiveurl=https://archive.is/vINCc|archivedate=13 April 2020|quote=Nope.}}

Players can donate dense essence blocks to [[Clerris]] in return for Arceuus [[favour]].

In order to use this mine, players require at least 25% Arceuus [[favour]] in addition to 38 [[Mining]] and 38 [[Crafting]]. A [[pickaxe]] and [[chisel]] in the player's inventory is required to mine the dense runestone, granting 12 Mining and 8 Crafting experience per block mined.

After completion of the medium tasks in the [[Kourend & Kebos Diary]], players have a chance to mine two dense essence blocks at once. No additional experience is awarded for the extra block.

While only 38 Mining is required to mine the essence, a higher Mining level is slightly helpful, as the essence stone depletes less frequently with a higher Mining level.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/973319634421239808|date=13 March 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/UTW2x|archivedate=25 May 2020|quote=Yes, slightly.}} At level 38 Mining there is a 85% chance to not deplete the dense runestone when successfully mining a dense essence block, increasing to 90% at level 99.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1057703180816080896|date=31 October 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/XJc0g|archivedate=25 May 2020|quote=82% -> 90% from 1 to 99}}

In order to use the shortcuts, you need to have 73 [[Agility]] for the western rock scramble, 69 for the northern scramble and 52 for the eastern scramble.

